    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-06T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="724"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4961: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CF1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-06T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>725. Yours and Strother’s telegrams of August 3 No. 2687 and the second
                    unnumbered [<hi rend="italic">26</hi>], announcing the evacuation of North
                    Russia.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>The Secretary of the Navy has been requested to keep the <hi rend="italic"
                            >Des Moines</hi> at Archangel.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>What accommodations will you require for Embassy and Consulate staffs and
                        American citizens? Are British arranging accommodations or could you all go
                        in <hi rend="italic">Des Moines?</hi>
                    </item>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>Regarding the evacuation of loyal Russians. Is Department to understand
                        that British are unable to supply accommodations for the 10,000 you mention
                        and, consequently, ask assistance from the United States? Your telegram not
                        clear on this point. Please furnish clear statement of how many it is
                        proposed to evacuate and who is to provide ships.</item>
                    <label>(4)</label>
                    <item>Consider this authority to evacuate Embassy and Consulate and American
                        citizens on such date as seems advisable after conference <pb facs="0759"
                            n="647" xml:id="pg_647"/> with your colleagues. In such event <persName
                            corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName> and Lee should proceed Washington,
                        Pierce granted leave and Strother proceed Amsterdam for temporary
                        duty.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
